import { Icon } from 'astro-icon';
---
<MainLayout>
    <section class="relative p-6 lg:p-6 grid gap-8 place-items-center lg:h-screen lg:content-center w-full md:w-2/3 lg:w-1/2 xl:w-1/3 mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center">
            <img class="w-48 h-48 mb-6 drop-shadow-xl rounded-full mx-auto" src="/images/kristi-portrait-square-2022.webp" loading="lazy" alt="portrait image" width="256" height="256" />
            <h1 class="font-serif italic text-2xl">Dr. Kristi Cash White, PhD, LPC</h1>
            <h2 class="font-bold text-base tracking-widest uppercase">Licensed Counselor</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
        <p>Mental health counselor virtually for the state of Oregon, in-person in East Portland. </p>
        <p>In my practice, it seems a lot of the focus these days is on transition. From teenagers figuring out who they are and young adults struggling to make a way to those in mid-life facing an empty nest and retirees asking themselves, "What now?" I work with people as they navigate life stages and reimagine their personal identities.  I believe in the healing power of connection, vulnerability, and relationship. I primarily utilize Adlerian, Acceptance & Commitment, Narrative, and Mindfulness theories and techniques as means to connect with and aid my clients.</p>

        <p><em>Session cost: $180</em></p>
        <p>Although I do not take insurance, I work with clients to put together the necessary paperwork for pursuing insurance reimbursement as an out-of-network therapist. Please check with your insurance carrier for applicable reimbursement rates.</p>
        <p>I am an Oregon-licensed counselor, supervisor, and professor with a Ph.D. in Counseling Education & Supervision from the University of the Cumberlands. I have 25 years of experience in the field with specialties in play therapy, public speaking, supervising counselors-in-training, and teaching.</p>

